-- Bolivian Government Seeks Release of Silver Workers, Cambio Says
-- B y   S a r a   S h a h r i a r i
-- 2012-07-05T15:53:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-05/bolivian-government-seeks-release-of-silver-workers-cambio-says.html
Bolivia Interior Minister Carlos
Romero said the government will not negotiate with the community
of Mallku Khota while it holds workers from a  South American
Silver (SAC)  unit, state daily Cambio reported, without saying where
it got the information.  Five people associated with the company are believed held
by the community in a conflict over mining concessions and the
arrest of a local leader, national outlet Radio Erbol reported,
without saying where it obtained the information.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sara Shahriari in La Paz at 
 sshahriari@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Goodman at   jgoodman19@bloomberg.net  